      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ISLAND YANKEE (1) was well fancied when resuming but manners let him down. Won his lone second-up attempt so should be improved. Likely to enjoy an economical run from this draw and has yet to miss a place in three attempts here including a win. DRAXON (10) made it three wins from his last five starts when he dug deep last time out at Shepparton, getting home by a head. Draws on the back line this time but has built a handy record at this distance and is going well. SPIRIT OF SAHARA (5) draws wider than when he placed last time at Shepparton but races well at this circuit and distance with a win and three placings from four attempts. LIT THE WICK (3) has been racing well and draws to make an impact again.",
